    "b-routing-elbow-p3-6": {
      "id": "b-routing-elbow-p3-6",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Whichever branch produces the route, waypoints are deduplicated ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "dedupeConsecutivePoints",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/routing/routing.ts",
              "symbol": "dedupeConsecutivePoints"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ") and turned into a rendered SVG path by "
        },
        {
          "insert": "roundedPolylinePath",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/routing/routing.ts",
              "symbol": "roundedPolylinePath"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", which rounds interior corners (clamped to half the shorter adjacent segment's length, so short segments still get a sane smaller radius rather than overshooting) and pulls the first/last rendered points back by a fixed end-gap along their own tangent so the drawn stroke never touches the target border — the connection's "
        },
        {
          "insert": "start",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "/"
        },
        {
          "insert": "end",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " fields still carry the true, untouched anchor points for endpoint-drag handles and label placement."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-routing-heading-anchor-7": {
      "id": "b-routing-heading-anchor-7",
      "flavour": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Anchor resolution"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-routing-anchor-p1-8": {
      "id": "b-routing-anchor-p1-8",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Before any path is computed, "
        },
        {
          "insert": "routeConnection",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/routing/routing.ts",
              "symbol": "routeConnection"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " decides which side of each endpoint object the connection attaches to. "
        },
        {
          "insert": "autoPickAnchors",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/routing/routing.ts",
              "symbol": "autoPickAnchors"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " compares the two objects' bounds centers and picks facing sides by whichever axis has the larger separation — right/left if the horizontal gap dominates, bottom/top otherwise — a nearest-side heuristic rather than an exhaustive search. This picked pair is only the fallback: an explicit "
        },
        {
          "insert": "connection.from.anchor",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "/"
        },
        {
          "insert": "connection.to.anchor",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " override (validated by "
        },
        {
          "insert": "explicitAnchor",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/routing/routing.ts",
              "symbol": "explicitAnchor"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " against the four "
        },
        {
          "insert": "top",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "/"
        },
        {
          "insert": "right",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "/"
        },
        {
          "insert": "bottom",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "/"
        },
        {
          "insert": "left",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " values) wins when set, and an explicit relative "
        },
        {
          "insert": "position",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (a "
        },
        {
          "insert": "[rx, ry]",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " fraction of an object's bounds, resolved by "
        },
        {
          "insert": "pointForPosition",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/routing/routing.ts",
              "symbol": "pointForPosition"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ") overrides even the anchor side entirely, landing the endpoint at a specific point rather than a side midpoint."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-routing-anchor-p2-9": {
      "id": "b-routing-anchor-p2-9",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The routing module also exposes two lower-level anchor helpers used elsewhere in the engine: "
        },
        {
          "insert": "anchorPoints",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/routing/routing.ts",
              "symbol": "anchorPoints"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " returns all four side-midpoints of a bounds, and "
        },
        {
          "insert": "nearestAnchor",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/routing/routing.ts",
              "symbol": "nearestAnchor"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " picks whichever of those four is closest to an arbitrary point — a plain bounding-box heuristic, distinct from the real-outline anchor projection the connection overlay performs (see below) for live drag/hover interaction."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-routing-heading-waypoint-10": {
      "id": "b-routing-heading-waypoint-10",
      "flavour": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Waypoint reconciliation on move"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-routing-waypoint-p1-11": {
      "id": "b-routing-waypoint-p1-11",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Explicit "
        },
        {
          "insert": "connection.waypoints",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (used by "
        },
        {
          "insert": "routeWaypoints",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/routing/routing.ts",
              "symbol": "routeWaypoints"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ") are stored as absolute world coordinates, so nothing in "
        },
        {
          "insert": "routing.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " itself keeps them coherent when an endpoint object moves — that reconciliation happens one layer up, in the action reducer. "
        },
        {
          "insert": "reconcileConnectionWaypoints",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/model/actions.ts",
              "symbol": "reconcileConnectionWaypoints"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " runs inside "
        },
        {
          "insert": "reduceInteractiveCanvasState",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/model/actions.ts",
              "symbol": "reduceInteractiveCanvasState"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — a choke point wrapped around every document-producing action (drag/section-carry commits, nudges, resize, align/distribute, fit-container, inspector geometry patches) — so the waypoint fix-up shares the action's own history entry and a single undo restores both geometry and waypoints together. "
        },
        {
          "insert": "canvas.undo",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "/"
        },
        {
          "insert": "canvas.redo",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "/"
        },
        {
          "insert": "canvas.reset",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " are exempt since they restore stored document snapshots verbatim."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-routing-waypoint-p2-12": {
      "id": "b-routing-waypoint-p2-12",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The reconciliation is asymmetric by design, per connection. For each waypointed connection, it compares its two endpoint owners' geometry before and after the action: if "
        },
        {
          "insert": "both",
          "attributes": {
            "italic": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " owners translated by the "
        },
        {
          "insert": "same",
          "attributes": {
            "italic": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " delta and neither resized — e.g. both riding a carried section, a multi-select drag, or a nudge — the waypoints translate rigidly by that same delta, preserving the connection's trunk-and-branch fan shape exactly. If only one owner moved, the two owners moved by different deltas, or either owner resized, the waypoints are dropped ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "undefined",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ") entirely so the connector falls back to auto-routing on next render rather than sweeping stale waypoints through space that's no longer meaningful relative to the shape — matching FigJam's re-route-on-asymmetric-move behavior. Duplicate and clipboard-paste actions handle the newly-created-object case separately, translating cloned waypoints by the paste offset at creation time rather than through this before/after comparison."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-routing-waypoint-p3-13": {
      "id": "b-routing-waypoint-p3-13",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "This rigid-translate/asymmetric-re-route split also applies to live-preview (non-history) drag frames, not just committed drags, so a fan of waypointed connectors visibly tracks a section as it's being dragged rather than only snapping into place on drop."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
